content:
Give underwriters easy access to loan application details to make informed decisions by using Underwriter Console. The underwriters can get a consolidated view of a submitted loan application on the application form product record page. They can view and edit assets, liabilities, and collateral details, assign action items, confirm pricing, verify integration results, such as Know Your Customer and credit checks, and approve or reject an application.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited editions where Financial Services Cloud is enabled. Digital Lending is available starting July 16, 2024. To use this feature, users need the Financial Services Cloud Extension, Financial Services Cloud Digital Lending, and Digital Lending Workbench permission sets.

Underwriter Console gives an underwriter a streamlined view of the loan application details without switching between tools. It’s time-consuming for an underwriter to use different tools to analyze an applicant’s credit history, verify income, submit supporting documentation, and gather personal data to determine if they qualify. Underwriter Console shows all these details in a single view, helping the underwriter save time and approve applications faster.

Set up Digital Lending self-service application intake and assisted application intake experience. Then, assign users the Digital Lending Workbench permission to give them access to digital lending underwriter console features.
title: Underwriter Console for Digital Lending
